No later than December 31 of each year, the Commissioner shall prepare an annual report about the previous fiscal year that includes:
a list of the authorized insurers transacting insurance business in the State, with any summary of their financial statements that the Commissioner considers appropriate;
the name of each insurer whose business was closed during the year, the cause of the closure, and the amount of assets and liabilities of the insurer that is ascertainable;
the name of each insurer against whom delinquency or similar proceedings were initiated, a concise statement of facts about each delinquency or similar proceeding, and the status of each proceeding;
a list of the rulings and decisions made in cases before the Administration during the year;
a statement of all fees, taxes, and administrative fines and penalties received by the Commissioner and deposited into the General Fund of the State;
the ratio of complaints filed during the calendar year against each insurer for each major line of insurance written by the insurer and a summary of the resolution of the complaints;
recommendations of the Commissioner about changes in the laws affecting insurance and about matters affecting the Administration;
information about the operation of the Fraud Division, including:
the number of complaints received that relate to insurance fraud, the nature of the complaints, and the resolution of the complaints;
the number of complaints and cases referred to a State's Attorney and the resolution of the complaints or cases;
the number of complaints and cases referred to the Office of the Attorney General and the resolution of the complaints or cases;
the number of calls made to the insurance fraud hot line;
the number of complaints received from persons regulated by the Commissioner;
the number of cases received from the Workers' Compensation Commission under § 9-310.2 of the Labor and Employment Article and the resolution of the cases;
the total number of cases, by type of insurance fraud; and
the number and percentage of cases that result in the imposition of civil or criminal penalties;
a list of all staff positions, classifications, and salaries in the Administration as of the end of the preceding calendar year; and
any other relevant information that the Commissioner considers proper.
